 IF you think former Minister of Aviation, Femi Fani-Kayode’s estranged wife, Precious Chikwendu, is still down or troubled following the messy separation with her husband, you may have to give it a second thought. If you want to confirm this, visit her Instagram page and see how she has been exciting her followers with her beauty and style.
It was all over the news in October that the couple separated after six years in marriage over allegations of infidelity and domestic violence.
The pretty lady seems to be enjoying her best life at the moment despite the media brouhaha the breakup created. She doesn’t even cut the picture of one who is worried or troubled.
Fani-Kayode married Precious in 2015, after three marriages. The union was blessed with four kids, including triplets.
Precious, who is from Etti-Nanka in Anambra State, is a model and actress. The second child of a family of seven, she graduated from the University of Calabar, Cross River State, where she obtained a Bachelor of Science degree in Environmental Science.